            <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #4A3B32; text-align: left; line-height: 1.5;">
                <p><strong>1. The Taste Score (T)</strong><br>
                For each variable <em>v</em> (Temp, Sweet, Intensity), a hidden parabola generates a score:<br>
                <span class="math-highlight">f(v) = a(v - h)&sup2; + k</span><br>
                Total Taste Score is the sum: <br>
                <span class="math-highlight">T = max(0, Round(f(t) + f(s) + f(i)))</span></p>
                
                <p><strong>2. Potential Customers (P)</strong><br>
                Based on Weather Demand (D) and Base Traffic (B):<br>
                <span class="math-highlight">P = Round(T &times; D &times; 1.5) + B + (5 &times; Buzz) + Modifiers</span><br>
                <em>Modifiers: +120 for Viral Perfect Snob Blog, +50 for Good Snob Blog, -30 for Bad Review, -150 for Price Gouging.</em></p>
                
                <p><strong>3. Conversion Rate (C) & Sales (S)</strong><br>
                Customers compare Taste (T) to Price (p) scaled by Price Sensitivity (Sens):<br>
                <span class="math-highlight">C = max(0, (T - (p &times; Sens)) / 100)</span><br>
                <span class="math-highlight">Sales = min(P, Round(P &times; C))</span><br>
                <em>Note: Heatwaves have a flat minimum conversion of 15% (0.15) due to desperation.</em><br>
                <strong>Anti-Exploit Cap:</strong> Pricing coffee over $20.00 triggers an automatic boycott (0 sales) and a -150 Customer penalty the following day.</p>
                
                <p><strong>4. Total Expenses & Marginal Cost</strong><br>
                <span class="math-highlight">Marginal Cost = (t &times; $0.10) + (s &times; $0.20) + (i &times; Bean Rate)</span><br>
                <em>Bean Rate is $0.50 standard, or $0.20 if Bulk Beans are in inventory.</em><br>
                <span class="math-highlight">Total Expenses = (Marginal Cost &times; Sales) + $150 Rent</span></p>
                
                <p><strong>5. Net Profit</strong><br>
                <span class="math-highlight">Net = (Price &times; Sales) - Total Expenses</span></p>

                <p><strong>6. Corporate Espionage (Sabotage) & Momentum</strong><br>
                Rival Base Profit: Sunny = $250, Heatwave = $350, Rainy = $150. Plus $2 compounding momentum every day.<br>
                To succeed in sabotage, the fake recipe's Taste Score (y) must beat their Suspicion Threshold.<br>
                <span class="math-highlight">Sabotaged Profit = Base &times; (y / k) - 100 &times; (1 - (y / k))</span><br>
                <em>If y = k (the perfect vertex), the rival is fooled into making 2.5x their base profit!</em></p>
            </div>
